SERVICE CLOUD
Set Visibility for the Chat Sessions Tab through Profiles

Session records store information about your agents’ and customers’ interactions online. Make the Chat sessions tab visible to users who are assigned to specified profiles.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Available in: Salesforce Classic, Lightning Experience, Performance Editions, Developer Edition orgs created after June 14, 2012, Essentials, Unlimited, and Enterprise Editions with Service Cloud or Sales Cloud

USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To set tab visibility for Chat sessions:	Manage Profiles and Permission Sets

IMPORTANT The legacy chat product is scheduled for retirement on February 14, 2026. To avoid service interruptions to your customers, migrate to Messaging for In-App and Web before that date.

From Setup, enter Profiles in the Quick Find box, then select Profiles.
Select a support agent profile.
Click Edit.
Set the visibility of the Chat sessions tab to Default On.
Click Save.
title: Set Up Service Cloud Chat Sessions Visibility
